(a)a person

 ("the lessor")

who grants leases of goods in the course of a business may agree on a percentage (other than nil) as the exempt percentage in relation to goods of a particular kind. The percentage agreed on must be the percentage of the statutory period during which it is agreed to be likely that the goods will be used by the lessor for lease (other than eligible long-term lease) to persons who, or whose sub-lessees, intend to use the goods during the whole of the term of the lease or sub-lease so as to satisfy one or more exemption Items;

